    "markdown": "---\nformat:\n  html:\n    css: styles.css\n    embed-resources: TRUE\n    code-fold: true\n    page-layout: full\n    fig_caption: yes\n---\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n::: narrow-section\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"grid-container\" style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); justify-items: center;\">\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">3,650</div>\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">6,109</div>\n<div style=\"display: block; &#10;              color: #ff6400; &#10;              font-size: 1.25em; &#10;              font-family: Graphik; &#10;              font-weight: bold; &#10;              text-align: center;\">NA</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Currently Eligible for<br>Parole but in Prison</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Eligible for Parole in<br>the next 1-5 years</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">\n<span class=\"tippy html-widget html-fill-item-overflow-hidden html-fill-item\" height=\"338px\" id=\"htmlwidget-76e9f28400c6476431a4\" width=\"100%\"></span>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-76e9f28400c6476431a4\">{\"x\":{\"opts\":{\"placement\":\"bottom\",\"flip\":true,\"theme\":\"light\",\"content\":\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Not Available<\\/b>: .\"},\"text\":\"<span aria-label=\\\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Not Available<\\/b>: .\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" role=\\\"button\\\">Prison Sentencing<br>System&#9432;<\\/span>\"},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n\n<br>\n\n\n\n::: panel-tabset \n\n## Parole Eligibility\n\n<center>\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">How is Parole Release Eligibility Determined?</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">Each crime in Louisiana appears to have a statutory maximum. For example, theft of something with a value of $25,000 or over will result in imprisonment of not more than twenty years or a fine of not more than fifty thousand dollars, or both. Any sentence to imprisonment must be “determinate,” in other words, judges sentence individuals to a maximum sentence rather than a range with minimum and maximum limits. Eligibility for parole is determined by type of crime and by criminal history. Unusually, prisoners who have been convicted of non-violent, non-sexual offenses can also age out of the Louisiana prison system even if they are ineligible for parole. If sentenced to a term of over 30 years, a prisoner who has served at least 20 of those years and has reached the age of 45 is eligible for parole consideration. If sentenced to any term without the benefit of parole, a prisoner who has reached the age of 60 and has completed various institutional requirements may be eligible for parole.</div>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">People who are Eligible for Parole</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"bar-chart\">\n<div id=\"htmlwidget-74337beb44c4e2274b71\" style=\"width:100%;height:454px;\" class=\"highchart html-widget \"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-74337beb44c4e2274b71\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\":{\"reflow\":true,\"width\":500,\"height\":350},\"title\":{\"text\":\"People who are Parole Eligible but Still in Prison by Race in 2020\"},\"yAxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":null},\"labels\":{\"enabled\":false}},\"credits\":{\"enabled\":false},\"exporting\":{\"enabled\":true},\"boost\":{\"enabled\":false},\"plotOptions\":{\"series\":{\"label\":{\"enabled\":false},\"turboThreshold\":0,\"animation\":false,\"cursor\":\"pointer\",\"borderWidth\":3,\"minPointLength\":4},\"treemap\":{\"layoutAlgorithm\":\"squarified\"},\"accessibility\":{\"enabled\":true,\"keyboardNavigation\":{\"enabled\":true},\"linkedDescription\":\"TBD\",\"landmarkVerbosity\":\"one\"},\"area\":{\"accessibility\":{\"description\":\"TBD\"}}},\"series\":[{\"group\":\"group\",\"data\":[{\"state\":\"Louisiana\",\"race\":\"Hispanic, any race\",\"n\":7,\"prop\":1,\"yearendpop_ped\":7,\"prop_label\":\"100%\",\"tooltip\":\"<b>Louisiana - Hispanic, any race<\\/b><br>100%<br>\",\"y\":100,\"color\":\"#440154\",\"name\":\"Hispanic, any race\",\"colorv\":\"Hispanic, any race\"}],\"type\":\"column\",\"dataLabels\":{\"enabled\":true,\"format\":\"{point.prop_label}\",\"style\":{\"fontSize\":\"14px\",\"fontWeight\":\"bold\",\"fontFamily\":\"Graphik\",\"textOutline\":0}}}],\"xAxis\":{\"categories\":\"Hispanic, any race\"},\"tooltip\":{\"formatter\":\"function(){return(this.point.tooltip)}\"},\"legend\":{\"enabled\":false}},\"theme\":{\"colors\":[\"#ff6400\",\"#ffaf00\",\"#c376fb\",\"#003474\",\"#00aba0\",\"#0061e4\"],\"chart\":{\"style\":{\"fontFamily\":\"Graphik\",\"color\":\"#3E4B4B\"}},\"title\":{\"align\":\"center\",\"style\":{\"fontFamily\":\"Graphik\",\"fontWeight\":\"bold\",\"color\":\"#3E4B4B\",\"fontSize\":\"18px\"}},\"subtitle\":{\"align\":\"center\",\"style\":{\"fontFamily\":\"Graphik\",\"fontWeight\":\"bold\",\"color\":\"#3E4B4B\",\"fontSize\":\"16px\"}},\"legend\":{\"align\":\"center\",\"verticalAlign\":\"top\",\"itemStyle\":{\"color\":\"#3E4B4B\"}},\"xAxis\":{\"labels\":{\"enabled\":true,\"style\":{\"color\":\"#3E4B4B\",\"fontWeight\":\"bold\"}},\"gridLineColor\":\"transparent\",\"lineColor\":\"transparent\",\"minorGridLineColor\":\"transparent\",\"tickColor\":\"transparent\"},\"yAxis\":{\"labels\":{\"enabled\":true,\"style\":{\"color\":\"#3E4B4B\"}},\"gridLineColor\":\"transparent\",\"lineColor\":\"transparent\",\"majorGridL